[DhtmlXQ_comment0]mm xqjwms sw 01020901 Pawn under attack||Intial analysis:||Black's chariot is threatening to capture the red pawn.||Should red try to protect the pawn with R2=3 or move the pawn out of harm's way, to the rib file where it can aid in attack?||This is an important issue to address.||After comparing various possibilities, we can safely come to the conclusion that if the red pawn was on the rib file, it could proceed to attack the palace with aid from the red cannon moving C2+1 (check). This is a very important point to take note off.||If the red cannon were on the left flank instead, moving the pawn to the rib file would not be so meaningful.||What about protecting the pawn?[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2]And the red pawn would be prevented from moving into the palace. ||Black would have the easier time in the game to come.[/DhtmlXQ_comment2]
